Anal papilla central; mouth marginal or submarginal; ambulacra running from arms to mouth via narrow tissue bridges. Ambulacra on proximal portion of arms (to beyond P 1 ) with sparse podia, apparently only 1–2 triads on each side of each brachial; triads accompanied by a pair of modified lappets with one saccule distal to lappet; lappet pairs sometimes resembling sessile pedicellaria (“pseudopedicellaria” of
Messing 2003
).
